@startuml
'title High Level Architecture

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

' ==============================
' Solution
' ==============================
package "PolyglotPlatform Solution" {

    component "PolyglotPlatform.Frontend\n(Blazor WebAssembly)" as FRONTEND
    component "PolyglotPlatfom.Api\n(ASP.NET Core Web API)" as API
    component "PolyglotPlatfom.Persistence\n(Class Library)" as PERSIST
    component "PolyglotPlatfom.Domain\n(Class Library)" as DOMAIN
}

database "SQL Server" as SQL

' ==============================
' Project References
' ==============================

API --> PERSIST : references
PERSIST --> DOMAIN : references

FRONTEND --> API : HTTP calls

' ==============================
' NuGet Packages
' ==============================

component "EF Core Design\n8.0.24\n<<NuGet>>" as EF_DESIGN
component "EF Core SqlServer\n8.0.24\n<<NuGet>>" as EF_SQL
component "Swashbuckle\n6.6.2\n<<NuGet>>" as SWAGGER
component "Blazor WebAssembly\n8.0.11\n<<NuGet>>" as BLAZOR

API ..> EF_DESIGN : uses
API ..> SWAGGER : uses

PERSIST ..> EF_DESIGN : uses
PERSIST ..> EF_SQL : uses

FRONTEND ..> BLAZOR : uses

' ==============================
' Runtime Flow
' ==============================

EF_SQL --> SQL : connects to

' ==============================
' Notes
' ==============================

note right of PERSIST
Contains:
- AppDbContext
- Migrations folder

Migrations are stored here
end note

note right of API
AppDbContext registered in Program.cs:
builder.Services.AddDbContext<AppDbContext>()

Connection string in:
appsettings.json

Migrations added & executed
from API (startup project)
end note

@enduml